parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning Blind Spot Detection System can cause false positive warnings, leading to undue concern and distraction while driving, potentially causing accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The Blind Spot Warning system reports false positives frequently
and causing the system to be unreliable and untrustworthy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dual Clutch Transmission (DCT) Failure to Shift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DCT to shift out of first gear can cause the engine to over-rev, leading to a potential loss of control, accidents, and engine damage.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift out of first gear
the vehicle may stall or hesitate.
